Please read the following informed consent document. Feel free to print a copy of consent for your records.



Consent Form Research Participant Informed Consent Form

Please read this document carefully before you decide to participate in this research study. Your participation is voluntary, and you can decline to participate, or withdraw consent at any time, with no consequences.



Study Title: Understanding E-learning Acceptance of Gen Z Students: An Extension of the Technology Acceptance Model (TAM)

Person(s) conducting the research: Dr. Sanaz Motamedi, ISE Department at UF

Email: smotamedi@ufl.edu

Phone: (401) 406-1720



Purpose: This study is being done to reveal the factors contributing to e-learning technology acceptance within Generation Z during COVID-19. Analysis from this focus group will shed light on the aspects of e-learning important to current university students.



What you will be asked to do? You will be asked to complete a questionnaire and share your thoughts about online learning.



Time required: This study will require no more than 20 minutes of your time.



Risks and benefits: There are no risks or discomforts anticipated as well as no direct benefits of participation for you.



Confidentiality: There is a minimal risk that security of any online data may be breached, but our survey host (QUALTRICS) uses strong encryption and other data security methods to protect your information. Only the researchers will have access to your information on the Qualtrics server. No identifying information will be collected or connected with your responses, which will be anonymous. However, even if any responses were to be disclosed outside of the research, the subject would not be at any risk. The participants in this study won’t be asked to disclose sensitive information and the questions aren’t harmful or offensive.



Compensation: It will not cost you anything to take part in this study nor will participation be monetarily compensated for.



Withdrawal from the study: You are free to withdraw your consent and to stop participating in this study at any time without consequence. You can decline to answer any question you don’t wish to answer. If you withdraw, your information will be discarded. If you wish to discuss the information above or any discomforts you may experience, please ask questions now or contact one of the research team members listed at the top of this form.



If you have any questions regarding your rights as a research subject, please contact the Institutional Review Board (IRB02) office (University of Florida; PO Box 100173; Gainesville, FL 32610; (352) 392-0433 or irb2@ufl.edu.)



Now that you’ve read about the study, if you wish to participate, click the “I agree to participate” button to continue; if you do not consent to participate, click “I do not wish to participate” or just close this window.
